President Biden addressed Sheet Metal Workers' Local 19 in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, on Labor Day. He thanked the labor unions for their support and emphasized his commitment to creating good-paying jobs and supporting the middle class. He highlighted his administration's efforts to invest in infrastructure, bring back manufacturing jobs, protect pensions, and ensure that corporations and the wealthy pay their fair share in taxes. He also discussed the importance of unions and the need to pass the PRO Act to protect workers' rights. President Biden expressed optimism about America's future and praised the hard work and determination of the American people.